The Dao that can be spoken is not the constant Dao.
The name that can be named is not the constant name.
Non-being is named as the beginning of heaven and earth;
being is named as the mother of the ten thousand things.
Thus, constant non-being: desire thereby to observe its subtlety;
constant being: desire thereby to observe its boundary.
These two emerge together but differ in name;
together they are called darkly profound.
Darkly profound and again darkly profound:
the gate of the many subtleties.

When all under Heaven know the beautiful as beautiful, then the ugly is already present;
when all know the good as good, then the not-good is already present.
Therefore being and non-being give rise to one another;
difficult and easy complete one another;
long and short give form to one another;
high and low incline toward one another;
tone and sound harmonize with one another;
before and after follow one another.
For this reason, the sage dwells in the work of without-action
and carries out the teaching without words.
The ten thousand things arise there, yet are not refused;
generated, yet not possessed;
acted, yet not relied upon;
the work accomplished, yet not dwelt in.
Precisely because it is not dwelt in,
therefore it does not depart.
